SWINE FEVER, CLASSICAL - SPAIN (03)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 25 June 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE [edited]
See Also
Swine fever, classical - Spain (02) 20010617.1168

Follow-up report No. 1
See also: 15 June 2001
Translation of information received on 19, 20, and 21 June 2001 from
Dr Ignacio Sanchez Esteban, Deputy Director General of Animal Health,
Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Madrid:
End of previous report period: 14 June 2001 (see Disease Information,
14 [24, 147, dated 15 June 2001).
End of this report period: 21 June 2001.
New outbreaks:
Location / No. of outbreaks
Golmes district, Lerida province, Catalonia Autonomous Community / 2
Mollerusa district, Lerida province, Catalonia Autonomous Community /
2
Vinaroz district, Castellon province, Valencia Autonomous Community /
1
Description of affected population in the new outbreaks: fattening
pigs (no breeding pigs).
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
species: sui
susceptible: 5143
cases: 630
deaths: 509
destroyed: 4634
slaughtered: 0
Control measures during reporting period:
- stamping out
- quarantine and movement control inside the country
- testing.
